<br>
When you see a chest spawn, stend up, target it and send in your pet.  You have to be standing or there's a good chance the chest will attack you instead, you also have to make sure you're sitting far enough away that the chest doesn't agro on you when it pops.<br>
<br>
Try to time your last nuke so the chest doesn't escape the ship, or it will be a pain to reposition your pet.<br>
<br>
Be warned, the chests have a LOT of hp and hit fairly hard, so you will need to keep a close eye on your pet's HP and also try to ration your mana usage very well.  If you spend too much mana nuking you won't be able to med back to full by the time the next chest spawns.<br>
<br>
There are two reasons to do it this way rather than swimming back to the beach<br>
1.  No sharks path near enough to the ship to attack you while you're in it.<br>
2.  You can spend more time medding if you don't swim to and from the beach.<br>
<br>
When I did this a few months ago the XP sucked, but it may be much better now with the pet XP changes.  The main reason to camp sea chests is they can drop most of the Velious quest gems (in fact, all except BP I think) whereas the Wyverns only drop the minor quest gems. <p><CENTER>
